The user updates his self-description as follows: I favor hook-first, tightly produced records — bright, clear mastering, layered vocal harmonies, punchy drums, and ear-catching melodic hooks. I enjoy modern synth-forward pop production but also appreciate classic rock/AOR greatest-hits that pair memorable riffs and concise, radio-ready arrangements with vintage analog warmth and charismatic, slightly gritty lead vocals (e.g., Steppenwolf). I gravitate toward mixes that reward focused listening, strong rhythmic drive, and concise songcraft. I dislike albums that prioritize brute distorted guitars, sudden visceral aggression, and live-immediacy over songwriting (as with sprawling prog concept albums like The Wall), jam-oriented sequencing that buries hooks, gravelly/shouty vocals that obscure melody, and muddy, midrange-heavy mixes that reduce clarity. 

